<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}-{8}{y}={13}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{5}{x}-{8}{y}={83}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({7},-{6}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+-{8}{y}={13}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}={13}-{\left(-{8}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{13}-{\left(-{8}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{5}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{\left(\frac{{{13}-{\left(-{8}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{5}}}}\right)}+-{8}{y}={83}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{5}}{{-{{5}}}}\cdot{\left({13}\right)}-\frac{{5}}{{-{{5}}}}{\left(-{8}\right)}{y}+-{8}{y}={83}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{13}-{\left(-{8}\right)}{y}+-{8}{y}={83}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{y}+{\left(-{8}\right)}{y}={83}--{13}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{y}+{\left(-{8}\right)}{y}={96}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{8}+{\left(-{8}\right)}\right)}{y}={96}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{16}{y}={96}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{96}}{{-{{16}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{6}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+-{8}{\left(-{6}\right)}={13}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{\left({48}\right)}={13}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}={13}-{\left({48}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}=-{35}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{35}}{{-{{5}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={7}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({7},-{6}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

